subtitles_text: >> JEFF PROBST: Previously on
Survivor... >> I'm not going to fight with
these kids. They hate us.
>> PROBST: When the fans' camp was filled with disarray...
>> Everyone is tired. Everyone is hungry.
>> We need to fix our shelter. >> PROBST: ...Joel was vocal
about getting the group back together.
>> Why is everybody talking all the time and not working?
>> PROBST: At Malakal, two couples came together
strategically and romantically, creating a formidable alliance.
>> I think we'll be receiving birth announcements from Ando
and her little Ozzlets that she's about to have.
And Parvati and James will be at the wedding as soon as this is
over. >> PROBST: Jonathan, Yau-Man,
Eliza, and Ami created a second alliance...
>> Hands in. I'll do it.
I'll do it. >> PROBST: And both sides needed
Cirie to gain a majority. >> I don't care.
I'll get rid of anybody, as long as it's not me.
>> PROBST: At the immunity challenge, the favorites won
easily. Favorites win immunity!
With the fans facing tribal council, Mikey B. attempted to
control the vote. >> Let's get the final plan
right now, and then we don't have to talk about it again.
>> PROBST: But after watching Mikey B. form a close bond with
Mary, Joel had other ideas. >> Mikey thinks he's running
this whole show. He and Mary have to be broken
up. Mary's going home.
Mikey will be completely confused as to what happened.
>> PROBST: At tribal council, Joel's plan worked.
Second person voted out of Survivor: Fans vs. Favorites,
Mary. And a stunned Mikey B. watched
his closest ally go home. 18 are left.
Who will be voted out tonight? >> Be careful right here, you
guys-- right here. >> I can only assume the big guy
Joel stuck a knife in my back already.
Interesting. I don't blame the move, okay,
you know, as long as the move is not you to take that whole crew.
That would be you with four girls and a kid, you know?
>> Yeah. >> And Chet is included as a
girl. Joel is playing a long game
right now when he should be focusing on a short game.
When it gets down to the merge, you get rid of the strong ones.
When it's team versus team, you keep your strength and you get
rid of your weakness. And these people-- Tracy, Kathy,
and Chet-- are weak around camp, and they're weak in the
challenges. They're all useless.
I know it's a million bucks, but you're not going to win with
them. I mean, you're not doing it.
>> Mikey thinks he's got all the answers, and he guarantees I'll
never make it to the final four, and he just thinks he's got this
whole tribe in his pocket. >> I consider it that you made a
move that you didn't have to make, okay, necessarily.
And you know, if you want to make up for it, you can.
>> And I would really, really like to see the look on his face
when the baseball bat comes swinging up beside him and wakes
him up to the reality that he doesn't have this tribe in his
pocket.  Captioning sponsored by
